# Dosecraft project rules

Dosecraft is a patient-facing infusion companion game, not a quiz app.

## Preserve core flows

- Preserve Companion Mode and infusion timer persistence (`dc_startTime`, `dc_durationMins`, `dc_endTime` in localStorage).
- Preserve intro → howToPlay → playing flow.
- Do not rewrite existing drug games.

## Implementation preferences

- Prefer reusing existing game mechanics before creating new ones.
- Keep language patient-friendly.
- Do not add dosing advice, cure claims, efficacy claims, or patient-specific medical advice.
- Avoid broad architecture changes unless explicitly requested.

## Adding a drug

Edit `drugCatalog.js` only — add the drug object and include its `id` in the appropriate `DOSECRAFT_DRUG_GROUPS` entry.

When adding a drug, list:

1. Changed files
2. Pharmacist-review items (description, howItWorks, encouragement, winMessage, intro/how-to-play copy)
